 《The Needle Drop》评论家安东尼·凡塔诺 (Anthony Fantano) 因披萨模因音频被动视公司起诉https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-needle-drop-critic-anthony-fantano-being-sued-by-activision-for-pizza-meme-audio-3473689?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=针滴评论家安东尼·凡塔诺因比萨模因音频而被动视公司起诉Liberty DunworthWed, 26 Jul 2023 12:25:58 +0000 Gaming NewsMusic NewsNewsActivisionTikTok https://www.nme.com/?p=3473689 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="2022 年 8 月 24 日，在科隆 Gamescom 视频游戏展上，一位参观者在三星移动展位上用手机玩动视的游戏《使命召唤》" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>该游戏公司声称他威胁要“滥用”知识产权法来起诉 TikTokers</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-needle-drop-critic-anthony-fantano-being-sued-by-activision-for-pizza-meme-audio-3473689">《The Needle Drop》评论家 Anthony Fantano 因披萨迷因音频被动视公司起诉的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="2022 年 8 月 24 日，在科隆 Gamescom 视频游戏展上，一位参观者在三星移动展位上用手机玩动视的游戏《使命召唤》" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/tiktok">TikTok</a>音乐评论家安东尼·凡塔诺 (Anthony Fantano) 因他在 2021 年开发的一段病毒式音频剪辑而被视频游戏巨头<a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/activision">动视 (Activision)</a>起诉。</p><p>该诉状由动视公司于周一（7月24日）向加州联邦法院提起，指控范塔诺“滥用”知识产权法，并威胁要起诉使用他的“足够切片！”音频的TikTok用户。模因。</p><p>该模因来自一段流行的音频剪辑，取自 Fantano 于 2021 年首次发布的视频之一。视频显示，当披萨被切成越来越小的切片时，评论家变得越来越恼怒，然后惊呼：“切片已经够多了！”。</p><p>上传两年来，它在网上获得了数千万的浏览量，并逐渐成为网络俚语，指的是情况开始良好但逐渐走得太远。</p><p>现在，动视暴雪提起诉讼，该品牌表示，在其<em>古惑狼</em>游戏系列的宣传中使用这段视频后，它受到了威胁。该诉讼还声称，“The Needle Drop”批评者故意将这段剪辑添加到 TikTok 的音频库中，以供用户使用，这意味着他无法起诉那些选择在自己的帖子中使用该剪辑的人。</p><p> “这场纠纷是个人如何滥用知识产权法来利用不公平现金支付的教科书例子，”动视暴雪的律师写道（来自<a href="https://www.billboard.com/business/legal/activision-suing-tiktok-music-critic-enough-slices-meme-1235377879/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em></a> ）。 “范塔诺非常高兴能够从公众使用 Slices 视频中受益。 It was only after he identified a financial opportunity — namely, receiving unjustified settlement payments — that he suddenly decided that his consent was limited.” </p><figure id="attachment_3473691" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3473691" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3473691" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Sign on facade of office of videogame publisher Activision in the Silicon Beach area of Los Angeles, California, December 10, 2018" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Activision-US@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3473691" class="wp-caption-text"> Sign on facade of office of videogame publisher Activision in the Silicon Beach area of Los Angeles, California. CREDIT: Smith Collection/Gado/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> They continued: “The law does not permit, and the court should not countenance, such overt gamesmanship,” as well as highlighting how he opted into the “Commercial Sounds” library – meaning he agreed his clip could be legally used in promotional videos for brands.</p><p> According to the outlet, the company received a threat of legal action from the TikTok star when it used the audio in a video about its custom <em>Crash Bandicoot</em> trainers. It was also allegedly told that it had not only “used his name-and-likeness rights without permission”, but had also “violated federal trademark laws by suggesting he had endorsed the company&#39;s games”.</p><p> While the clip was taken down by Activision, the brand claims that Fantano still demanded the company “either immediately pay him substantial monetary damages”, which was reported to be a six-figure sum, or be “prepared to defend a lawsuit”.</p><p> Rather than agreeing to pay the sum, it responded by filing the lawsuit at the start of the week, saying that neither the company nor other TikTok users owe Fantano any money from using the clip.</p><p> The suit is seeking a “declaratory” ruling that the music critic cannot sue users over the clip, and also demands he repay the company&#39;s legal bills.</p><p> “With Fantano&#39;s approval and encouragement, hundreds of thousands of TikTok users have incorporated the Slices Audio into their own videos over the past two years,” the company&#39;s lawyers wrote (via <a href="https://www.billboard.com/business/legal/activision-suing-tiktok-music-critic-enough-slices-meme-1235377879/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em></a> ). “But now … Fantano has embarked on a scheme whereby he selectively threatens to sue certain users of the Slices Audio unless they pay him extortionate amounts of money for their alleged use.”</p><p> <em>NME</em> has reached out to Anthony Fantano for comment through his website.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-needle-drop-critic-anthony-fantano-being-sued-by-activision-for-pizza-meme-audio-3473689">&#39;The Needle Drop&#39; critic Anthony Fantano being sued by Activision for pizza meme audio</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
